STEP 1:
Open terminal & Install ESP tool by using the command - 
pip install esptool

STEP 2: Eraise the alredy flashed firmware in the esp8266 board type - 
esptool.py --port /dev/ttyUSB0 erase_flash


If you face an error like this " [Errno 13] Permission denied: '/dev/ttyUSB0' " If not ignore
 
 Type the command
 
 sudo su
 //type your password
 cd /
 cd dev
 chown username ttyUSB0

then ctrl -D to exit from the root



STEP 3: Download the micropthon firmware from the website - https://micropython.org/downloadhttps://micropython.org/download
          in this site download the  latest fiemware for esp8266

STEP 4: Then go to the folde where the the download bin file of the fiwmware located then type
        
        esptool.py --port /dev/ttyUSB0 --baud 460800 write_flash --flash_size=detect 0 esp8266-20170108-v1.8.7.bin
        
        you need to change "esp8266-20170108-v1.8.7.bin" as the name of the downloaded file name
        
        For some boards with a particular FlashROM configuration (e.g. some variants of a NodeMCU board) you may need to use the following command to deploy the firmware (note the -fm dio option):
        
        esptool.py --port /dev/ttyUSB0 --baud 460800 write_flash --flash_size=detect -fm dio 0 esp8266-20170108-v1.8.7.bin
        
        you need to change "esp8266-20170108-v1.8.7.bin" as the name of the downloaded file name
        
        
      
